SQL_STMT_U.val: delete from :1/T203 A where A.T203_RUNNUMBER = :2 and exists(select * from :1/T203 B where B.T203_RUNNUMBER = :2 and B.T203_LINENO <> A.T203_LINENO and B.T203_REINSCLNT_CONTRACTNR = A.T203_REINSCLNT_CONTRACTNR and B.T203_REINSURANCENUMBER = A.T203_REINSURANCENUMBER and B.T203_REINSURANCELIM > A.T203_REINSURANCELIM)

Text.val: -- Step 1. Define client numbers where limits could exist
... reset variables
... delete temporary table (collects clients to handle)
-- Delete T203 row (part of step "9. Row handled ")
-- Set/Reset variables
-- Negative credit check
-- Step 2. Reinsurance number does not exist / try with registration nr
-- Step 3. Reinsurance number exists / test registration number
-- Step 4. Reinsurance number exists / registration number handled
-- Step 9. Row handled
... set main client (of frist selected client)
... select individual clients
... store individual clients to temp table, used in further steps of BDC405

Header.Description: Select DEBC rows with old limi

Text.val: (see extra range ctrl + H)
if debtor is on erorr list (duplicate debtor for example) the (old) limit should
not be removed
find the last line number
write new row in temp table for BXA031 --> "Debtor is no longer monitored"
-- Continue with step 3 (reinsurance already exists)
-- Continue with step 9 (Unknown (empty) company registration numnber)
-- Test if debtor can be selecetd via external ID
... add the reinsurance number and continue with step 3
... continue with step 9 ( both the reinsurance number and the registration
number are unknown)
-- Continue with step 4 ( both the reinsurance number and the registration
number are unknown)
-- Check if there exists a row in DHIC with another registration number
-- Check to add the correct registration number
... continue with step 4 (correct registration number is already present)
... if not present it can be added if the validation is OK
... continue with step 4 (registration number is wrong)
... continue with step 4 (registration number already exist)
... registration number does not exist
.. perform duplicate check, perhaps the number already exists for another debtor
... store the new registration number and continue with step 3
-- A row is present (with another registration number), it is too dangerous to
update the limits, so inform the users and continue with step 9
-- A row is present, we'll not add the registration number to prevent duplicates
if T203_CREDIT_CHECK='L' the client is no longer insured - limit has to be
removed (NULL)
-- Only one DEBC row was selected leave BDC405A else check which limit should
remain
-- A limit is present at the main client, go on to clean the limit and
limit history which are defined for individual clients
-- Determine DEBC_NO for further updates
... get first DEBC_NO with fully test criterias
. if not exist, try to find a debtor at the main client (reduced test criterias)
. if not exist, try to find a debtor at the individual client level (reduced
test criterias)
A. Update TEMP_ODC_CHANGESBYFILE
-- If the old and new reinsurance limits are equal, set status = 9, changes must
not be reported via BXA031
B. Update in DEBTOR_CLIENT
if limit is temp limit - set expirry date
C. Store row in DEBTOR_REINSURANCE_HISTORY
if limit is temp limit we stor two rows in history one for fixed amount and one
for the fixed amount + the temp amount
D. Store row in table SILO trigger invoice buying
... T203 is deleted physically in parent task
... only if all T203 rows were handeld
